This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with image analysis and saliency map detection. Additionally, the use of semantic segmentation as a high level feature suggests that the paper may also belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The use of fusion techniques and simulation results suggest that the paper may also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories. Finally, the use of image recognition and classification techniques suggests that the paper may also belong to the information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category.
